= PUPPET MODULE:
  sudo

== REQUIREMENTS:

=== Platform and Application Environment:

Tested on Ubuntu 12.04. May work on other platforms, esp Ubuntu/Debian.

== USAGE:

# Simple default install

class { 'sudo' : }
include sudo

# Absent (but not purged)

class { 'sudo' : packageensure => 'absent' }

# Uninstalled (and purged)

class { 'sudo' : packageensure => 'purged' }

# Non-default sudoers

class { 'sudo' : sudoers => hiera('sudoers_prod') }

# Default install but call sudo::config::sudoers for additional sudoers

include sudo
sudo::config::sudoers { 'jack' : }

== CAVEATS:

The class will fail if if cannot find the necessary sudoers under the puppet
file resource. The order of search is the following:
puppet:///modules/sudo/$::{lsbdistcodename}/$::{hostname}/${name}
puppet:///modules/sudo/$::{lsbdistcodename}/$::{role}/${name}
puppet:///modules/sudo/$::{lsbdistcodename}/${name}
puppet:///modules/sudo/${name}

